# Monorepo Structure and Management

- Follow Turborepo conventions for monorepo structure
- Use pnpm for package management
- Maintain clean separation between packages and apps
- Use consistent versioning across the monorepo
- Share types and utilities through the shared package
- Avoid unnecessary dependencies between packages
- Follow consistent naming conventions across packages
- Implement proper workspace configuration
- Use consistent build and development scripts
- Implement proper dependency management between packages
- Avoid duplication of code across packages
- Use proper package exports and imports
- Follow consistent documentation patterns
- Implement proper testing for each package
- Use consistent tooling across the monorepo